Locals love to keep the 19 miles of beach a secret, because it's one of the few areas in the state where you don't have to search long and hard for parking spots or fight for the perfect place to pitch your umbrella and beach chairs. Once settled in, you'll enjoy the cinnamon-colored sand that sparkles with fragments of limestone crystals and of course, the breathtaking view of the Atlantic Ocean.

Events must take place in Palm Coast and the Flagler Beaches, be open to the public, and must be one of the following types of events:
Art Shows, Performing Arts Productions/Events, Musical Performances/Concerts, Exhibits/Related Events, Professional and High-Profile Sporting Events, Special Activities such as Circuses, County-Wide Festivals and Parades, Wine Tasting Events, Attraction-Hosted Events, High Profile National Speakers.
Fill out the fields below in order to have your events listed in our online calendar. Please note: Your event will not automatically be added to the calendar once you click "Submit Event" at the bottom of the form. It will first go through an approval process to make sure that it contains all the information needed to be added.
For questions on photo and event submissions, please contact Christina Hutsell at chutsell@visitflagler.com or 386.313.4228.

Check out our list of events that occur throughout the year. With a variety of events that appeal to athletes, foodies, art-lovers, and families, you're sure to find something fun to do in the Palm Coast and Flagler Beaches!
Click on a month to be taken to the events that usually happen then. For more events, head over to our
events calendar
.
Monthly
Food Truck Tuesdays - Every other month starting in March on 3rd Tuesday
Free Movies in Central Park - Second Fridays
First Fridays in Flagler Beach
Second Saturday Plant Sale
Palm Coast Farmer's Market - Every Sunday. 12 p.m. to 4 p.m. at European Village
Flagler Beach Farmer's Market - Every Saturday, 9 a.m. -1 p.m.
January
USTA-Men's Futures Tennis Tournament
February
Race the Runways
Palm Coast Strawberry Festival
Native American Festival - Princess Place Pow Wow
March
Bike Week
Warbirds Over Flagler
April
Turtle Fest
Flagler County Fair and Youth Show
Earth Day Celebration
Easter Egg’stravaganza
May
Cycle Flagler
May Day Surf Classic
Songwriters Festival
Brian Earl Foster Invitational Bull Riding
Bunnell Bonanza
Hang 8 Dog Surfing Competition
June
Father's Day Invitational Lacrosse Tournament
Florida Lacrosse Showcase
July
United Flagler Fourth
Flagler Beach Fourth of July Parade
August
Surfers for Autism
October
Biketober Fest
The Pink 5K Run & 1 Mile Walk
Kix Country Fest
Creekside Music & Arts Festival
Corvette Show
Hall of Terror
Witches and Warlocks of Flagler Beach Bike Ride
November
Spoonbills and Sprockets Cycling Tour
Thanksgiving Feet to Feast 15K/5K Run/Walk
Freedom Fest
December
Starlight 5k Bridge Run
Holiday at the Beach and Annual Christmas Parade
Palm Coast Holiday Boat Parade
Holiday in the Gardens at
Washington Oaks Gardens State Park

The Flagler County Tourist Development Council (TDC) is offering a Special Event Marketing Grant (SEMG) to provide assistance to organizations for the marketing of special events that promote Flagler County as a tourist destination. Funds available through this program must be used for expenditures associated with marketing and promoting an event to attendees outside of Flagler County, with the goal of increasing overall economic impact and/or overnight stays in Flagler County.
Funding is still available for events that take place from October 1, 2024 - September 30, 2025.
This program requires participation in a
(pre-recorded) Grant Workshop
. The SEMG Workshop, along with a competitive application process, enables Palm Coast and the Flagler Beaches to provide funding. These funds are on a first come first serve basis so do not wait to apply. If you have any questions or need assistance, please contact Christina Hutsell at 386-313-4228 or
Chutsell@visitflagler.com
.
SEMG Workshop Slides
If you have questions or would like staff to review your application before submitting, please contact Christina Hutsell at (386) 313-4228 or chutsell@visitflagler.com.
